It seems, Gallery is not properly cleaning up package upload state after sync validation failure:

0. Need latest dev with `Gallery.RejectPackagesWithLicense` flag in (#6562);
1. Enable the flag;
2. Start Gallery;
3. Try to upload .nupkg with <license> in it, Gallery rejects it;
4. Stop Gallery, disable the flag, start it again;
5. Go to upload page;

At this point Gallery suggests to continue with package upload (that previously failed), which means that package that was previously considered invalid was still stored. I'm not sure this is expected behavior.

Currently if you have a transitive projects, the transitive project will have a requested version for the project. 
This would mean every project version change will require a lock file regeneration. 

